---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
	title="man joe | Joe Karlsson"
	description="The manual page for Joe Karlsson. Because every good engineer needs documentation."
>
	<div class="man-wrapper">
		<div class="man-terminal">
			<!-- Terminal header bar -->
			<div class="man-titlebar">
				<div class="man-dots">
					<span class="man-dot man-dot-red"></span>
					<span class="man-dot man-dot-yellow"></span>
					<span class="man-dot man-dot-green"></span>
				</div>
				<span class="man-titlebar-text">man joe</span>
				<div class="man-dots" style="visibility: hidden;">
					<span class="man-dot"></span>
					<span class="man-dot"></span>
					<span class="man-dot"></span>
				</div>
			</div>

			<!-- Man page content -->
			<div class="man-content">
				<pre
					class="man-pre"><span class="man-header">JOE(1)                          User Commands                          JOE(1)</span>

<span class="man-section">NAME</span>
       joe - software engineer, developer advocate, massive nerd

<span class="man-section">SYNOPSIS</span>
       <span class="man-bold">joe</span> [<span class="man-underline">OPTIONS</span>...] [<span class="man-underline">PROJECT</span>]

<span class="man-section">DESCRIPTION</span>
       Joe Karlsson is a software engineer turned developer advocate who has
       spent the last decade working on databases, real-time data, IoT, and
       developer tools. He has spoken at over 100 conferences, given a TEDx
       talk, and built an IoT-connected cat litter box that he is probably
       too proud of.

       Currently doing developer relations at CloudQuery. Previously at
       Tinybird, SingleStore, and MongoDB. Before DevRel, was a front-end
       technical lead at Best Buy and a full-stack JavaScript instructor.

<span class="man-section">OPTIONS</span>
       <span class="man-bold">--verbose</span>
              Enable long-form storytelling about homelabs and databases.
              Warning: may not shut up about Proxmox.

       <span class="man-bold">--homelab</span>
              Activate homelab mode. Deploys 40+ containers, sets up
              Proxmox cluster, configures Home Assistant, and wonders
              why the electricity bill is so high.

       <span class="man-bold">--cats</span>
              Enable IoT cat monitoring. Connects litter box to Raspberry
              Pi. Generates conference talk material.

       <span class="man-bold">--film</span>
              Activate Letterboxd integration. Will have opinions about
              every movie you mention.

       <span class="man-bold">--debug</span>
              Increases coffee intake. Decreases sleep. Standard
              engineering tradeoff.

<span class="man-section">ENVIRONMENT</span>
       <span class="man-bold">EDITOR</span>=neovim
       <span class="man-bold">SHELL</span>=/bin/zsh
       <span class="man-bold">CONTAINER_RUNTIME</span>=docker
       <span class="man-bold">HOMELAB_STATUS</span>=always-tinkering
       <span class="man-bold">CATS</span>=2
       <span class="man-bold">COFFEE_LEVEL</span>=critical

<span class="man-section">FILES</span>
       <span class="man-underline">~/.config/homelab/docker-compose.yml</span>
              The file that started it all. Now 847 lines long.

       <span class="man-underline">/var/log/3am-decisions.log</span>
              A growing record of questionable infrastructure choices
              made after midnight.

       <span class="man-underline">/etc/cron.d/gpu-transcode</span>
              Automated GPU transcoding jobs. Yes, at 2am. On purpose.

<span class="man-section">BUGS</span>
       Buys too many hard drives. Cannot stop adding containers.
       Occasionally mass-assigns GPU transcoding jobs at 2am.
       Has mass-reassigned a variable name in production and called
       it "refactoring." Will talk about homelabs unprompted.

<span class="man-section">HISTORY</span>
       2015-2017    Full-Stack JavaScript Instructor, DevLeague
       2017-2019    Front-end Technical Lead, Best Buy
       2019-2021    Senior Developer Advocate, MongoDB
       2021-2023    Senior Developer Advocate, SingleStore
       2023-2025    Developer Advocate, Tinybird
       2025-present Developer Advocate, CloudQuery

<span class="man-section">SEE ALSO</span>
       <span class="man-underline">joekarlsson.com/about</span>, <span class="man-underline">joekarlsson.com/work</span>, <span class="man-underline">joekarlsson.com/blog</span>
       GitHub: <span class="man-underline">github.com/JoeKarlsson</span>
       Bluesky: <span class="man-underline">@joekarlsson.com</span>

<span class="man-section">AUTHOR</span>
       Written by Joe Karlsson, with mass-assistance from mass-caffeine.

<span class="man-header">JOE(1)                          March 2026                          JOE(1)</span></pre>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
	.man-wrapper {
		display: flex;
		justify-content: center;
		padding: 2rem 1rem;
	}

	.man-terminal {
		width: 100%;
		max-width: 52rem;
		border: 1px solid #2a2d34;
		border-radius: 0.5rem;
		overflow: hidden;
		background-color: #0a0a0f;
		box-shadow:
			0 25px 50px -12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5),
			0 0 0 1px rgba(42, 45, 52, 0.3);
	}

	.man-titlebar {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: space-between;
		padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
		background-color: #111318;
		border-bottom: 1px solid #2a2d34;
	}

	.man-dots {
		display: flex;
		gap: 0.5rem;
	}

	.man-dot {
		width: 0.75rem;
		height: 0.75rem;
		border-radius: 50%;
	}

	.man-dot-red {
		background-color: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.8);
	}

	.man-dot-yellow {
		background-color: rgba(234, 179, 8, 0.8);
	}

	.man-dot-green {
		background-color: rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.8);
	}

	.man-titlebar-text {
		font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', 'Fira Code', Menlo, Monaco, monospace;
		font-size: 0.75rem;
		color: #8bcbc8;
	}

	.man-content {
		padding: 1.5rem;
		overflow-x: auto;
	}

	.man-pre {
		font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', 'Fira Code', Menlo, Monaco, monospace;
		font-size: 0.875rem;
		line-height: 1.6;
		color: #d1d5db;
		white-space: pre;
		margin: 0;
		tab-size: 8;
	}

	.man-header {
		color: #fdae84;
		font-weight: bold;
	}

	.man-section {
		color: #ffffff;
		font-weight: bold;
	}

	.man-bold {
		color: #ffffff;
		font-weight: bold;
	}

	.man-underline {
		text-decoration: underline;
		text-underline-offset: 2px;
	}

	@media (max-width: 640px) {
		.man-wrapper {
			padding: 1rem 0.5rem;
		}

		.man-content {
			padding: 1rem;
		}

		.man-pre {
			font-size: 0.7rem;
			line-height: 1.5;
		}
	}
</style>
